author: WSJ Staff
title: Shock Election Result Spells Turbulence For Malaysian Markets
text:
Heavy selling looms in Malaysian assets when markets reopen next week, after the country’s opposition coalition pulled off a shock victory in Wednesday’s election.
A U.S.-listed exchange-traded fund of Malaysian stocks slumped 6% on Wednesday, its biggest decline since 2011, while the dollar has risen more than 2% against the ringgit in the derivatives market.
